## DETAILED IMPLEMENTATION PLAN: Opinion Viewer and Reply Card Redesign

### OVERVIEW

The goal is to transform `opinionViewer.jsx` and `OpinionsCardRepy.jsx` from their current bare, unstyled state into polished components that match the PostCards design system: card containers with borders and hover effects, CSS variables throughout, proper typography hierarchy, Framer Motion animations, and dark mode support via the existing `[data-theme="dark"]` token system.

---

### PART 1: JSX CHANGES FOR `opinionViewer.jsx`

**File:** `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\SidebarOpinions\opinionViewer.jsx`

**New imports to add at the top:**

```jsx
import { motion, AnimatePresence } from "framer-motion";
import formatPostDate from "../../../helpers/formatDateString";  
// Note: the import path from PostCards.jsx uses "../../../../helpers/formatDateString"
// but opinionViewer is one level shallower: SidebarOpinions/ vs HomePage/postCards/
```

**Complete new JSX structure** (replacing lines 67-109):

```jsx
return (
  <>
    {opinionData?.map((opinion, index) => (
      <motion.div
        className="ov-parent"
        key={opinion.id}
        initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 12 }}
        animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
        transition={{ duration: 0.3, delay: index * 0.05 }}
      >
        {/* ── Main opinion card ── */}
        <div className="ov-card">
          {/* User info row: avatar + name + dot + date */}
          <div className="ov-user-row">
            <div className="ov-avatar-wrap">
              <img
                className="ov-avatar"
                src={opinion.users.image_url || '../assets/profile.jpg'}
                alt=""
              />
            </div>
            <div className="ov-user-meta">
              <span className="ov-username">{opinion.users.name}</span>
              <span className="ov-separator">&bull;</span>
              <span className="ov-date">{formatPostDate(opinion.created_at)}</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          {/* Opinion body text */}
          <div className="ov-body">
            {opinion.opinion}
          </div>

          {/* Metadata bar: reply count pill + full date */}
          <div className="ov-meta-bar">
            <div className="ov-reply-pill">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth="2" strokeLinecap="round" strokeLinejoin="round">
                <path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/>
              </svg>
              <span>{opinion.reply_count} {opinion.reply_count === 1 ? 'reply' : 'replies'}</span>
            </div>
            <span className="ov-full-date">
              {new Date(opinion.created_at).toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
                month: 'long',
                day: '2-digit',
                year: 'numeric',
              })}
            </span>
          </div>

          {/* Reply input area */}
          <div className="ov-reply-input-row">
            <img
              className="ov-reply-avatar"
              src={user?.userData[0].image_url || '../assets/profile.jpg'}
              alt=""
            />
            <div
              className="ov-reply-input"
              onFocus={() => setIsTyping(true)}
              ref={textAreaRef}
              value={replyOpinion}
              onInput={(e) => setReplyOpinion(e.currentTarget.innerText.trim())}
              data-placeholder={`Reply to ${opinion.users.name}...`}
              contentEditable="true"
              role="textbox"
            />
          </div>

          {/* Submit/Cancel buttons */}
          <AnimatePresence>
            {isTyping && (
              <motion.div
                className="ov-actions"
                initial={{ opacity: 0, height: 0 }}
                animate={{ opacity: 1, height: 'auto' }}
                exit={{ opacity: 0, height: 0 }}
                transition={{ duration: 0.2 }}
              >
                <button
                  className="ov-btn ov-btn-cancel"
                  onClick={(e) => cancelTyping(e)}
                >
                  Cancel
                </button>
                <button
                  className={`ov-btn ov-btn-submit ${replyOpinion.trim().length === 0 ? 'ov-btn-disabled' : ''}`}
                  disabled={replyOpinion.trim().length === 0}
                  onClick={() => submitReply(opinionId, userId, user?.userData[0].id, opinion.id)}
                >
                  Reply
                </button>
              </motion.div>
            )}
          </AnimatePresence>
        </div>

        {/* ── Nested replies ── */}
        <div className="ov-replies-section">
          <OpinionsReplyCard opinionId={opinion.id} depth={0} />
        </div>
      </motion.div>
    ))}
  </>
);
```

**Key structural changes:**
- Wrap the entire parent in a `motion.div` for entry animation (opacity 0 to 1, y 12 to 0 -- matching PostCards pattern)
- Replace the 50px avatar with a 32px avatar in a wrapper div (to allow badge ring styling later)
- Add a PostCards-style user info row: name + dot separator + relative date
- Move the email display out (it clutters the header; the username is sufficient)
- Wrap the opinion body in a dedicated `.ov-body` div for serif typography
- Convert metadata into a bar with a pill-shaped reply count and a faint full date
- Wrap the reply input in a card-style row with proper alignment
- Add `AnimatePresence` around the submit/cancel buttons for smooth show/hide
- Pass a `depth={0}` prop to `OpinionsReplyCard` to enable nesting indentation

